def format_meter(n, total, elapsed, ncols=None, prefix='', ascii=False,
                 unit='it', unit_scale=False, rate=None, bar_format=None,
                 postfix=None, unit_divisor=1000, **extra_kwargs):
    # sanity check: total

    if total and n > total:
        total_limit = None
    else:
        total_limit = total
    
    # apply custom scale if necessary
    if unit_scale and unit_scale not in (True, 1):
        total_scaled = total_limit * unit_scale
        n_scaled = n * unit_scale
        if rate:
            rate *= unit_scale  # by default rate = 1 / self.avg_time
            unit_scale = False
    
    format_interval = tqdm.format_interval
    elapsed_str = format_interval(elapsed)
    
    # if unspecified, attempt to use rate = average speed
    # (we allow manual override since predicting time is an arcane art)
    if rate is None and elapsed:
        rate = n / elapsed
    inv_rate = 1 / rate if rate else None
    format_sizeof = tqdm.format_sizeof
    rate_noinv_fmt = ((format_sizeof(rate) if unit_scale else
                       '{0:5.2f}'.format(rate))
                      if rate else '?') + unit + '/s'
    rate_inv_fmt = ((format_sizeof(inv_rate) if unit_scale else
                     '{0:5.2f}'.format(inv_rate))
                    if inv_rate else '?') + 's/' + unit
    rate_fmt = rate_inv_fmt if inv_rate and inv_rate > 1 else rate_noinv_fmt
    
    if unit_scale:
        n_fmt = format_sizeof(n_scaled, divisor=unit_divisor)
        total_fmt = format_sizeof(total_scaled, divisor=unit_divisor) \
            if total else None
    else:
        n_fmt = str(n)
        total_fmt = str(total)
